    "drop": false,
    "field": "finance",
    "role": "agent",
    "bullets": [
      "Synthetic UK loan book of 1,200 credit applications, framed as an intake-to-settlement underwriting workflow with priced external data sources.",
      "An agentic engine treats each information purchase as a Pandora's box, pricing vendor fees plus large-language-model tokens; the model family is not stated and outputs are not checked against ground truth.",
      "Cost per decision falls 38.7 percent, from 33.54 to 20.57 pounds, with lower regret than a perfect-information oracle, worth about 1.3m pounds a year at 100,000 applications."
    ],
