    "uid": "arxiv:2606.26959v1",
    "drop": false,
    "field": "economics",
    "role": "object",
    "bullets": [
      "Usage data from OpenAI's Codex tool over the first half of 2026, contrasting external personal-account users, external organizational-account users, and workers inside OpenAI.",
      "Codex, OpenAI's agentic coding tool in the GPT family, is the object of study; an automated privacy-protecting pipeline measures adoption, sophistication, and output rather than using the model to read documents.",
      "Active users grew more than fivefold in the first half of 2026, over 10 percent run three or more concurrent agents weekly, and the median OpenAI researcher produced over 50 times more monthly output tokens than in November 2025."
    ],
